RiskSeverityMitigationINTELLECT_HOME env var leak between turnsHighfinally block in _run_agent ensures restoration even on exceptionAgent cache growth (N profiles × M sessions)MediumPer-profile cache cap, configurable via MultiProfileConfigConfig merge surprises (profile overrides gateway)Low_deep_merge preserves all base keys; profile only overrides what it declaresProfile not found (deleted from disk)Lowget_profile_config returns empty dict on missing config.yaml, graceful degradation to base configSQLite lock contention (frequent profile lookups)LowProfileRouter.resolve() opens a short-lived SessionDB() and closes it immediately; WAL mode ensures concurrent access
Edge Cases

Profile deleted while Gateway is running — next message to that profile falls back to base config (graceful degradation).  Logs a warning.
Binding created while user is mid-conversation — takes effect on the next message, not the current turn.
config.yaml has YAML syntax errors — yaml.safe_load exception is caught, returns empty dict, logs warning.
Multi-profile disabled mid-session — ProfileRouter.enabled is read on every resolve() call.  If disabled via hot-reload, subsequent messages use the default profile.  Cached per-profile agents are not cleaned up until Gateway restart or idle TTL eviction.
SessionDB unavailable — resolve() returns default_profile.  The Gateway can still process messages with its own config as a single-profile fallback.
